column2:
"Bootcamp Resources: 

Percipio Users: Open a new tab in your browser first, and then follow the steps to find resources and then follow these steps.

Step 1. Log into Percipio
Step 2. Select Library > Showcase > Skillsoft Bootcamps

column2:
Q1. I have a question about attendance, how it works, if I need to use the attendance tracker, and how do I get my certificate of completion. Where can I find the answers  to these questions?

A1. At the beginning of each session the instructor will review the attendance requirements. You can also watch the Day 1 lunch video for information about attendance. The Day 5 video will explain the options for getting your certificate. You can access these videos here.

https://github.com/Skillsoft-Content/PMP5Day/tree/main/Lunch%20Break%20Videos

The attendance tracker .docx file contains all the details including what the attendance tracker is, why it needs to be used, how to fill it in, and if you need to do anything with it to get your certificate. The tracker document is called: PMP Bootcamp 5-Day and 8-Day Attendance Tracker and Certificate Request Process.docx. You can download it from here.

https://github.com/Skillsoft-Content/PMP5Day/tree/main/5-Day%20Attendance%20and%20Certificates%20of%20Completion%20Info

column2: Hi all, good evening... @Carl can u plz brief about the learner kit requirement? when will it be needed?
column5:
As long as you have it before you submit your application to PMI you are fine. All participants in Skillsoft’s ATP-authorized PMP Bootcamps who intend to sit for the PMP exam are required to have a PMP Learner Kit. Your training staff or HR Department for your company should be helping to facilitate the purchase of the learner kit by contacting your company's Skillsoft Account Executive who will provide them with your access key. If there is no process setup for them and they are asking you to purchase it on your own, you can start the purchase of the Learning kit from this web site by clicking on the Buy button. You will be redirected to another page to make the purchase.
 
https://www.skillsoft.com/pmp-voucher-offering

column2: what is considered a package?
column5:
A planning package is a work breakdown structure component below the control account with known work content but without detailed schedule activities

A work package is the work defined at the lowest level of the work breakdown structure for which cost and duration are estimated and managed.

column2: Can we say Critical path is the shortest way to complete any task
column5: Can we say Critical path is the shortest way to complete any task

column2: Can we say Critical path is the shortest way to complete any task
column5: The critcal path is the longest path in the diagram. But it represents the shortest time the project can be completed. Any other path in the network diagram wouldn't take into account all the time required to complete the project. And if the tasks on the critical path take longer to complete it could result in even more time to complete the project unless something is done to get the project back on track.

column2: What are the forward and backward pass?
column5:
Forward pass - Going from left to right you determine the early start and early finish dates for each acivity.

Backward pass - Starting at the end going from right to left you determine the late finish date and late start date for each activity.

Backward pass - Starting at the end going from right to left you determine the late finish date and late start date for each activity.

Float - The difference between the early and late dates.

column2: Carl, sorry to keep harping on this, but I have now received 2 different emails from 2 different people from PMI as well as a phone call with a live PMI agent and I am 3 for 3 on them telling me the only required purchase is the exam itself, so I am getting very confused, ha-ha. column5: All I can tell you is what I have been told. For an organization and their training to be authorized as an ATP as part of the application process, the learner kit is required. This is documented as part of the ATP agreement between Skillsoft and PMI. And so, all participants in Skillsoft’s ATP-authorized PMP Bootcamps who intend to sit for the PMP exam are required to have a PMP Learner Kit. This Learner Kit is not required for participants who are attending the Bootcamp for reasons other than taking the exam, such as expanding their project management knowledge, or earning continuing education credit.

column2: Can you review critical path calculation again, specifically why we do not use a backward path calculation?
column5: Can you review critical path calculation again, specifically why we do not use a backward path calculation?

column2: Can you review critical path calculation again, specifically why we do not use a backward path calculation?
column5:
If you are filling out the full diagram you do both a forward pass and a backward pass.

Forward pass - Going from left to right you determine the early start and early finish dates for each acivity.

Backward pass - Starting at the end going from right to left you determine the late finish date and late start date for each activity.

A shortcut is to just add the durations for each path to see which has the longest duration. The path with the longest duration is the critical path

column2: Question about the 60 hours of project experience needed with an Associates. I had my own staffing business and ran each search as a project. I was solo so I don't have proof to show but did my work like this for 10 years. How can I justify this on the application?
column5: Question about the 60 hours of project experience needed with an Associates. I had my own staffing business and ran each search as a project. I was solo so I don't have proof to show but did my work like this for 10 years. How can I justify this on the application?

column2: Question about the 60 hours of project experience needed with an Associates. I had my own staffing business and ran each search as a project. I was solo so I don't have proof to show but did my work like this for 10 years. How can I justify this on the application?
column5:
Here are a few important things to keep in mind when filing out your application.

1. The work has to include aspects of project management such as managing scope, schedule, budget, quality, risk, procurement, stakeholders, etc.
2. Make sure they way you describe your project experience is not too technical in detail that the person reviewing your application wouldn't understand your project management work experience.
3. Check the following exam content outline to get an idea of the types of tasks that would be acceptable for the application as well as the PMP Eligibility Requirements.

https://www.pmi.org/-/media/pmi/documents/public/pdf/certifications/pmp-examination-content-outline.pdf

column2: Often in job description scrum master have a role of pm. Why?
column5: Often in job description scrum master have a role of pm. Why?

column2: Often in job description scrum master have a role of pm. Why?
column5:
According to the Scrum Guide, "Scrum
defines three specific accountabilities within the Scrum Team: the Developers, the Product Owner, and
the Scrum Master."

https://scrumguides.org/docs/scrumguide/v2020/2020-Scrum-Guide-US.pdf#zoom=100

The PM and Scrum Master have different accountabilities. Not sure why the job description you are seeing would have the Scrum Master playing the PM role unless they don't understand what the accountabilities of a Scrum Master entails OR they want someone to have two different accountabilities.
